  "response": "Google can typically detect and scan links shared through Gmail or Facebook plugins for several purposes:\n\n1. Gmail:\n- Google can see and analyze links in email content\n- Links are scanned for potential phishing or malware threats\n- The scanning helps protect users from potentially harmful websites\n\n2. Facebook Plugin:\n- Google can generally access and index publicly shared links\n- Links shared through Facebook's plugins may be crawled by search engines\n- The visibility depends on privacy settings of the post\n\nHowever, the full extent of link tracking depends on:\n- Link visibility settings\n- Privacy configurations\n- Whether the link is public or private\n- Specific platform policies\n\nKeep in mind that while Google can often detect links, the depth of information gathered can vary based on context and accessibility.",
